neighborhood_overview:
Orange is a beautiful city distinguished by its gorgeous tree-lined streets, charming heritage houses and fresh local produce. Home to just over 40,000 people, this significant regional centre hosts an exciting calendar of events including festivals of food and wine, cycling, running, hot-air ballooning and poetry along with regular farmers markets and much more.
Over 80 vineyards surround Orange and produce distinguished cool-climate wines made with passion by our resident winemakers and vignerons. The city is also known for its lovely parks, brilliant autumn colours, vibrant café’s and award winning restaurants.
host_about:

All of our properties are well maintained, contain high quality and fresh linen, essential amenities and are thoroughly cleaned and prepared for our next guests following our strict cleaning protocols.

We are a team of 4 who all grew up in and adore our wonderful region. All of our guests receive our local guide which provides fantastic tips to cafes, restaurants, boutique shopping, vineyards, outdoor activities + more! 
Thank you for choosing our home and we can't wait to host you!

neighborhood_overview:
Avalon - Whale Beach is as beautiful, sleepy area with the Coffee "Graze N Cakes" on the Burrawong Road (off Carreel Bay Road) is the nearest place to get coffee.

Cranzgotts Pizza around the corner on Barrenjoey is also good.

Heading towards Avalon on Barrenjoey Road is the nearest Servo - open till 9pm usually. Cheapest place for fuel on the Northern beaches (usually.)

Best place for Breakfast ( I think) is Relish a bit further towards Avalon on North Avalon Road. This is also the nearest bottle shop.

There is a cafe down at Whale Beach - but its not ON the beach so sort of defeats the object!

There are public BBQ's at Whale beach - nice for breakfast or later in the afternoon.

To get to the beach/pool at Whale beach simply turn left out of the house and after about 8 mins walk turn right on Malo road, there is a path down to the beach at the bottom on the left. (10 mins)

Walk to north Avalon is a bit trickie

The gourmet kitchen is integrated into the main living and entertaining area and is fully equipped and fitted w
neighborhood_overview: Warriewood Beach is one of the lesser known beaches on the peninsula, but as a result is one of the more relaxed and undeveloped. Situated between Mona Vale to the north, and the ‘hidden’ Turimetta Beach and pretty North Narrabeen to the south, Warriewood is backed by steep cliffs with a rocky headland and nature reserve to the south. At low tide, Mona Vale Beach is accessible via Warriewood Beach, offering a great evening walk along the sands. There are a number of laid back cafes and restaurants above the beach, catering for locals, families, surfers and tourists enjoying a great holiday spot. Northern Beaches Holidays offers several stylish family holiday rental houses at Warriewood.

neighborhood_overview: Our region is blessed with magnificent beaches, fresh locally grown food and the great outdoors.  Enjoy a laid back lifestyle, with friendly people, where keeping fit, enjoying life and preserving nature surrounding us is paramount.
host_about:
Hi! i am Susan de Jonge and moved from Sydney to the Port Macquarie area in 2014 after falling in love with the area and a local man.  I started my own holiday acommodation business along the Port Macquarie coastline called mySOLscape (escape to the sun) so guests can discover and enjoy the area too!  I live in the beautiful coastal town of Bonny Hills just south of Port. I have traveled the world and lived in Europe, USA and China and have made Australia my home now, my roots are Dutch.  I spent 7 years in Sydney working in the professional service industry and was commuting back and forth between Port Macquarie and Sydney for the past years.
Bonny Hills was and will always be my city escape with a permanent holiday feel, you can't beat nature around here, you will find unspoiled and uncrowded beaches, with city conveniences still nearby (Port Macquarie 20-25 min drive).
I am trying to keep fit on the trails and beaches, love bush adventures and scuba diving. I also like cooking fresh food, guests can treat themselves to the herbs and veggies in the garden of certain properties. My mantra: if you don't go, you don't see. Why; why not?

neighborhood_overview:
Avalon Beach is a beautiful suburb of Sydney's northern beaches. There is a gorgeous village of shops with boutique clothing stores, several bottle shops, Woolworths plus many divine cafes and restaurants. Avalon Beach still feels like a small beach-side village with a great buzz. We have lived here our whole life and love it!

Avalon Beach was named after the mythical Avalon, a legendary island in Celtic languages mythology. According to legends, Avalon was an earthly paradise and the final resting place of King Arthur.

There are other beaches within minutes' drive - Palm Beach, Whale Beach, Bilgola Beach and Clareville. You have Palm Beach lighthouse up the road, beautiful Pittwater where you can hire boats, catch the ferry to the pristine Basin or simply drive 2 minutes up the road and drop a fishing line off a wharf at either Paradise Beach or Taylors Point wharf.

host_location: Port Stephens, New South Wales, Australia
host_about:
Winning Hollidays are holiday rental specialists in the Port Stephens area and with over 30 year's experience our guests can relax, knowing they have booked quality accommodation through a trusted management team.  Offering hundreds of self-contained houses, apartments and villas from humble beach shacks to stunning waterfront locations, we are sure to have something to suit your needs. 

Showcasing a bay twice the size of Sydney Harbour and home to over 26 stunning white sand beaches, Port Stephens is a holiday mecca for those who love surf, sand and sea.  Home to an amazingly diverse marine life, like dolphins and migrating whales during the season, Port Stephens has boundless opportunities to get outside and explore its pristine waterways. If you love snorkeling, cycling, bush walking, kayaking, sailing, golf, eating out, local breweries, five-star dining, parasailing, quad-biking, horse-riding and spectacular sunsets then you will love Port Stephens.

Further afield you will find the many award-winning vineyards of the Hunter Valley or the exciting city of Newcastle.

By car, Port Stephens is approximately 2.5 hours north of Sydney and only 20 minutes from Newcastle Airport.

host_location: Port Stephens, New South Wales, Australia
host_about:
Winning Hollidays are holiday rental specialists in the Port Stephens area and with over 30 year's experience our guests can relax, knowing they have booked quality accommodation through a trusted management team.  Offering hundreds of self-contained houses, apartments and villas from humble beach shacks to stunning waterfront locations, we are sure to have something to suit your needs. 

Showcasing a bay twice the size of Sydney Harbour and home to over 26 stunning white sand beaches, Port Stephens is a holiday mecca for those who love surf, sand and sea.  Home to an amazingly diverse marine life, like dolphins and migrating whales during the season, Port Stephens has boundless opportunities to get outside and explore its pristine waterways. If you love snorkeling, cycling, bush walking, kayaking, sailing, golf, eating out, local breweries, five-star dining, parasailing, quad-biking, horse-riding and spectacular sunsets then you will love Port Stephens.

Further afield you will find the many award-winning vineyards of the Hunter Valley or the exciting city of Newcastle.

By car, Port Stephens is approximately 2.5 hours north of Sydney and only 20 minutes from Newcastle Airport.

neighborhood_overview:
Fingal Bay is still a sleepy little beach town, with many beaches to explore. Some can only be accessed via a bush walk where you will see many of our wildflowers, spring is a magical time to view the wildflowers.

The main beach has a surf club and a restaurant with views you can only dream about. When the whales come through they can be seen while you are enjoying a meal at the restaurant.

There is a small little shopping village with cafes and eateries that supply some of the best food in Port Stephens.
Fingal Bay is a great area to walk or ride a bike around with more hidden gems, The Spit is something to explore (walking only), timing with the tides is required to get to island on the other side. Shelly beach is a spectacular find on this island along with the old lighthouse.

The beach trails offer endless areas to explore, you can ride your bike or walk. The trails take you from Fingal Bay to Shoal Bay where there are many restaurants and bou
host_location: Anna Bay, New South Wales, Australia
host_about:
I love helping people discover Port Stephens, a delightful holiday destination only two hour’s drive north of Sydney. I have managed a range of holiday properties, from budget to boutique, for the last 10 years giving me unique knowledge and insight to match the needs and expectations of guests and property owners alike.
Please see the range of extra services and recommendations offered, including hampers and styling advice. 

For Guests: 
I understand different people have different needs when it comes to booking a holiday, I offer a personalised service for each of my guests. I understand and respect all guests have specific expectations and endeavour to match guests with appropriate properties. Correspondence and confirmation is available by phone, text and email.
All my properties supply linen; sheets, pillow cases, bath towels, bath mats, hand towels and tea towels. You only need to bring your beach towel, although we can arrange hire of these too!
Properties are fully self-contained with complete kitchens, outdoor BBQ, laundries, bedrooms and lounge/dining rooms. Some include private yards, balconies and unrivalled views. 
Units, duplexes and houses are all available, depending on your requirements and preferences in Fingal Bay, Shoal Bay and Fisherman’s Bay.
Since moving to Port Stephens whale watching has become a passion for me, whether I’m watching from the shoreline or on board a whale watching charter. Whale season is between June and October, with dolphins inspiring us all year round. 
Fisherman’s Bay: You can sit on the balcony or in the lounge room and see the whales come by, a truly magnificent site.
Pet Friendly: Some family members have paws, if that’s your family take a look at our Fingal Bay property. There’s even a nearby dog park!
Hampers: Picnic baskets, gift boxes and fresh flowers can also be organised for your special occasion, anniversary, birthday or just because you want something a bit special. Charter bookings for dolphin/whale watch cruises and deep sea fishing can also be organised.
All properties are professionally cleaned prior to your arrival. Check in is easy so you can enjoy your stay as soon as you arrive.
For Owners:
I have lived in Port Stephens for over 25 years and have managed over 180 holiday properties in the last 10 years. I have experience in what does and does not work in our local market and provide advice to all my owners for setting up a holiday property to balance the needs and wants of owners and guests. My management style is friendly and personalised for each owner, providing regular updates, statements and payments. 
Your property is unique, just like you, and I believe when you enhance the property’s personality you encourage guests to return to your property for future holidays in the Bay.

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Clovelly is a beautiful, family-friendly neighbourhood nestled between Coogee and Bronte in Sydney's Eastern Suburbs.

Less than 100 metres from our house, we have the main Clovelly shops which offer an array of cafes, shops including, Clodeli, Green Mango, The Village (excellent cafes!), Vintage Cellars (Bottle shop), news agency, convenience store, post office, laundromats and beauty and hair salons.

A few suggestions:
Bronte to Bondi Coastal walk (you can start at Clovelly though)
Coogee Pavillon is a great family restaurant/bar - fantastic pizza and is right on the water at Coogee.

name: Apartment near the beach and city!
description:
Our apartment is perfectly located for an easy walk to Bronte and Clovelly beaches as well as quick access to the City via Bondi Junction transport interchange. Local cafes and shops aplenty too.

Enjoy the relaxed green spaces of Centennial and Queens Parks too also a short walk away.

The space
Our home is the perfect pad for your getaway in Sydney. All mod cons, north facing balcony, hard wood floors and kitchen-diner set up in a small quiet block

Guest access
Wifi
FOXTEL HD incl. Sports,
North facing balcony and BBQ
Separate Laundry

Other things to note
5 night minimum stay
neighborhood_overview:
Beachy neighborhood vibe combined with convenient and quick access to the City and green oasis that is Centennial Park!

Local shops and eateries are on your doorstep on Macpherson St, including hotspots 3 Blue Ducks, Iggys and Moxhe, and on Albion St with Vacanza, Bellagio Cafe and Uyen.

A pleasant stroll to Bronte and Clovelly beaches awaits you pr take a short bus ride to Bondi Beach or Coogee Beach.
